res, packrat middens, tree rings, and archaeological sites. A perfect guide for students, scholars, travelers, and general readers alike, the book weaves together history, archaeology, botany, geology, biogeography, and other disciplines into one compelling panorama across a truly unique American landscape.  aMode of access: Internet via World Wide Web.  aIn English.0 aDescription based on online resource; title from PDF title page (publisher's Web site, viewed 29. Mai 2023) 0aGeologyzGreat Basin. 0aGeology, StratigraphicyHolocene. 0aGeology, StratigraphicyPleistocene. 0aIndians of North AmericazGreat BasinxAntiquities. 0aPaleo-IndianszGreat Basin. 0aPaleontologyzGreat Basin. 7aNATURE / Environmental Conservation & Protection.2bisacsh  aamerican west.  aanimals.  aarchaeological sites.  aarchaeology.  abiogeography.  abison.  abonneville salt flats.  abotany.  acalifornia.  aclimate.  adeath valley.  aecosystem.  aenvironment.  aenvironmentalism.  ageology.  aglaciers.  agreat basin.  agreat salt lake.  ahistory.  aindigenous people.  alake cores.  alake tahoe.  alakes.  anatural history.  anature.  anevada.  aoregon.  apackrat middens.  apaleontology.  arivers.  ascience.  atree rings.  autah.  awildlife.08iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertUniversity of California Press Backlist Package 2000-2013z97831106904220 cprintz978052026747340uhttps://doi.org/10.1525/978052094871640uhttps://www.degruyter.com/isbn/9780520948716423Coveruhttps://www.degruyter.com/document/cover/isbn/9780520948716/original  a978-3-11-069042-2  University of California Press Backlist Package 2000-2013c2000d2013  aEBA_FAO  aEBA_UCA_YUP  aGBV-deGruyter-alles  aZDB-23-UCY